<h2>South Calgary Homes</h2>
<p>South Calgary was established in 1914, but was largely undeveloped until the 1950&rsquo;s. The Greater South Calgary area consists of the communities of Marda Loop, Riverpark Altadore, Garrison Woods and South Calgary, all of which are under the care of the Marda Loop Community Association, which collectively unites the communities into a closely linked network. The shared community sense between South Calgary&rsquo;s adjacent communities makes it a friendly community and a great place for a family.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="footnote" style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Arial;"><span style="font-family: 'lucida grande', 'lucida sans unicode', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 20px;">South Calgary Real Estate Listings Community #017</span></p>
<p>Calgary Real Estate Quadrant: SouthWest Calgary<br />Similar neighboring communities of <a href="/richmond.php" target="_self">Richmond</a>, <a href="/bankview.php" target="_self">Bankview</a> and <a href="/altadore.php">Altadore</a>.<br />Community Established 1914 <br /><br />The real estate district of South Calgary offers some of the best mix of inner city in-fills and established vintage homes for the money in Calgary. The South Calgary community contains selection of housing ranging from small condo and apartment buildings to spanning bungalows and attractive period homes. This variety is typical of 1950's development and adds to the eclectic and personalized feel of the properties. <br /><br /><strong>South Calgary Schools</strong><br />King Edward Elementary and Junior High - Public<br />Altadore Elementary - Public<br />Calgary Waldorf School - Private<br />Glenmore Christian Academy - Private<br />Lycee Louis Pasteur &ndash; Private</p>
